Making screen backgrounds guide


1. Duplicate the main text
2. Click on it with the text tool (big A) and change what it says
3. View -> Show Grid and Snap to Grid
4. Right click main text layer, click alpha to selection
5. Select -> Grow -> 2 px -> ok
6. New layer (transparency)
7. Fill it with white with the bucket tool
8. Put it under the main text layer
9. Duplicate main text
10. MOve it to the left for a black offset
11. Show the original pre-existing text layer
12. Set the foreground and background colors at the top and bottom with the eyedropper tool
13. Select main text layer
14. Select gradient tool
15. Click on top of any letter and click again on the bottom  to make gradient
16. Done!